events.name: Gravel w/ Power Take Off
events.info: -Gravel is a Traditional Hard Rock / Radio Rock band based out of Colorado Springs, Colorado. Gravel is known for their extensive Tour Schedules, doing over 200 shows a year Nation Wide going from Coast to Coast and Border to Border. Their single All I Want From their Freshman Release Lets Do This went to #22 on the Nation Wide SMR FM Rock Charts and is currently in the running to be charting on the Nation Wide Billboard Charts.-The Birth of Power Take Off: A Band Built on Family and DeterminationThe story of Power Take Off begins in 2019, in the midst of global uncertainty. As the world grappled with the challenges of the pandemic, Scott Theis (vocals) and his son Ayden Theis (drums) transformed their basement into a creative haven, where they began writing music together. What started as a father-son project quickly evolved into something biggeran energetic and dynamic band with a mission to captivate audiences.Scott, a fourth-generation farmer and truck driver, has always balanced his passion for music with his work. His career as a drummer took him across the U.S., but Power Take Off marks his debut as a lead vocalist. His son Ayden, now 17, brings a youthful energy and exceptional talent to the drums, following in his fathers musical footsteps. Together, theyve created the foundation of Power Take Offs sounda blend of classic rock influence with modern pop punk vibes.The duo soon expanded, adding guitarist Ethan Hank Schluter, guitarist Mike Cowboy Delp, and bassist Jakob JR Ripp. Each member brings their own musical experience and style, creating a well-rounded and energetic sound that defines the bands identity.

boxOfficeInfo.openHoursDetail: The Solvay Bank Box Office at The Oncenter is located on the State Street side of The Oncenter War Memorial Arena (760 S. State St.). To purchase tickets or for more information, you can call 315-435-2121. The Solvay Bank Box Office at The Oncenter is open Monday thru Friday from 10:00 a.m. to 5:00 p.m. and Saturday from 9:00 a.m. to 1:00 p.m. (closed Saturdays in the summer) The Solvay Bank Box Office at The Oncenter is closed on Sunday. During weekend events, the box office will open in the theater lobby one (1) hour prior to the start of the show.
